You mean Renderman is not a ray-tracer... It uses shaders to create 
its images. A friend told me how shaders work generally and how they are 
used.

I don't think Renderman ray-traces 100%... Then again, all ray-tracing 
programs (except for some very slow ones) are not real ray-tracing 
programs because they use tricks to speed up the process. A common one is 
terminating a RAY that comes from (or rather goes to, if you want to think 
about it that way) the sky rather than tracing it through the atmosphere 
until it reaches the sky. 

@endnode

